definition: to wake up/to be awake/to become aware/to sober up/to come to

sentences.english: Attempt to do me awake all the way, Xinxin Ran opened his eyes.

sentences.english: All look like the appearance which just awoke, joyfully opened joyful enlarged ones vision.
sentences.chinese: 一切都象剛睡醒的樣子，欣欣然張開了眼。

sentences.english: When she woke up, she told me my fats made the best pillow ever.
sentences.chinese: 她睡醒以後說，我的肚腩當枕頭真是絕了。

sentences.english: Becuase I often lose my confidence, I decide tell myself 'go' in front of mirror after getting up every day.
sentences.chinese: 所以我要每天早上睡醒後對着鏡子說一遍加油。

sentences.english: Everything seems to be awaken from sleep, opening his eyes drawlingly.
sentences.chinese: 一切都像剛睡醒的樣子，欣欣然張開了眼。

sentences.english: Moon, you must be tired and didn't wake up.

sentences.english: Let the second hand suspend, awakes from the samsara, loves thorough.
sentences.chinese: 讓秒針暫停，從輪迴中睡醒，愛個徹底。

sentences.english: Natasha waked up and saw Sonya.
sentences.chinese: 娜塔莎睡醒了，看見索尼婭。

sentences.english: The shadows had not fled, the citizens of Jerusalem had not awaked. It was still night--the hour of sleep and darkness, when He arose.
sentences.chinese: 黑夜還沒有退去，耶路撒冷的市民還沒有睡醒。

sentences.english: Venus has not awake, our flag had been floating in the wind wax wax ring.
sentences.chinese: 啓明星還沒睡醒，我們的旗幟已在風中臘臘飄響。

sentences.english: It seems that everything is just after a long sleep, their eyes still sleepy.
sentences.chinese: 一切都像剛睡醒的樣子，欣欣然張開了眼。

sentences.english: And Jacob awaked out of his sleep, and he said, Surely the LORD is in this place; and I knew it not.
sentences.chinese: 雅各睡醒了，說，耶和華真在這裏，我竟不知道。

sentences.english: Do they now need to wait hours for you to wake up and build it?
sentences.chinese: 他們現在需要等待數小時，等您睡醒，然後構建嗎？

sentences.english: Strolling along the boulevard, one feels as if the West Lake were wakening in dawn mist.
sentences.chinese: 信步長堤，仿若西湖從霧靄中剛睡醒似的。

sentences.english: Jim listlessly streeked his limbs after wake-up.
sentences.chinese: 吉姆睡醒之後伸展四肢，讓自己清醒過來。

sentences.english: Wake up HanShan first saw hanging in the head of a bed photos, ghastly a smile.

to wake up from a sleep
